@node intro "Introduction"

 	What is it for?

        Fast and small CLI program to build unix "hoover" script.
        Mainly for Aminet FTP places.
        Why I made this? This is perfect for ME (own headers).
              	

        o Yet another program to do the same thing :)
        o Two CED scripts to help this work.
        o !!!You can add own headers to script.!!!
        

@endnode

@node requires "Requirements"

        Requirements?

        Any kind of Amiga and OS 2.04 or better.
        
        I have A3000/6MB/OS3.1

@endnode

@node using "Using"
	
	Using?


	Usage: AmiRec Recentfile Outputfile <Header>

        @{"Recentfile" link recent} is filename of ASCII text.

        @{"Outputfile" link output} is filename of ready ASCII script.

        <Header> is filename of ASCII text <- Not needed.
    

        !! New feature in V1.2 !!

        If ya want to get .readme instead of binary:

        DisplayModeV121.lha  util/misc   16K+Screenmode preferences V1.21 (CardWare)
                                           ^
                                           ^

        Change K, M or ? to R - then file readme is taken.
         
        
        ----

        Example of header file. It is added before script.
 
        #!/bin/sh

        host=ftp.luth.se
        ftp -n -i $host << EOF
        user anonymous $USER@
        binary

@endnode

@node Output "Output"

	Output?


 	cd /pub/aminet/util/misc
	get DisplayModeV121.lha
	cd /pub/aminet/util/wb
	get CXHandlerV25.lha
	EOF

@endnode

